{"type":"message","id":"ad6d8e0f","parentId":"620a5e1f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:41:05.491Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4kuz228boo2h_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 144040\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and what action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and insights:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. CFI Compression experiment is done - showed CFI gives +32.9% precision but loses 92.9% recall\r\n3. Key finding: constant format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts with zero information content\r\n4. Next experiment pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Need to run 200 pulses, 80/20 split\r\n\r\nThe most logical next action is to run the hybrid scoring experiment that was identified as the next step. This would involve creating a test script or documenting the experiment protocol.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists:\r\n- `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` - the experiment results\r\n- Need to run the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take is to set up the experiment protocol or begin executing it. Since I need to be specific and prefer file edits, I should either:\r\n1. Create an experiment protocol document\r\n2. Modify the existing pulse script to test this new formula\r\n3. Create a test script for the hybrid scoring\r\n\r\nGiven the context, the most valuable next step is to set up the hybrid scoring experiment. I could create a small test script or protocol document that defines how to run this experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, looking more carefully - the pending item is to \"Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\". But running 200 pulses would take ~116 minutes (at 35s per pulse). That's a lot.\r\n\r\nA more practical first step would be to:\r\n1. Create a test/validation script that can evaluate the formula on the existing data\r\n\r\n\r\n2. Or create a smaller pilot experiment\r\n\r\nI'll focus on developing a validation script for the hybrid scoring approach. The script will systematically test the proposed formula against existing pulse data, providing a quick way to assess its effectiveness before committing to a full 200-pulse experiment. This approach allows for rapid iteration and potential refinement of the scoring method.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) is the clear next step - it addresses the constant-format token problem identified in the CFI synthesis. I need to create a test harness that validates whether `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` distinguishes metaprogramming artifacts from meaningful research tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a validation script to test the hybrid scoring formula against the existing pulse corpus. This will be a quick sanity check before committing to a full 200-pulse experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Validation\r\n# Test: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Goal: Does this distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"?\r\n\r\n$baseDir = (Get-Item $PSCommandPath).Parent.Parent\r\n\r\n# Load corpus stats from CFI synthesis\r\n$cfiDoc = Get-Content \"$baseDir/research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\" -Raw\r\n\r\n# Token categories to validate\r\n$testCases = @(\r\n    # Constant format tokens (should score LOW despite high CFI)\r\n    @{Token=\"for next instantiation\"; Freq=160; CFI=1.00; Expected=\"LOW\"}\r\n    @{Token=\"pulse\"; Freq=160; CFI=1.00; Expected=\"LOW\"}\r\n    @{Token=\"completed at:\"; Freq=160; CFI=1.00; Expected=\"LOW\"}\r\n    \r\n    # Research trajectory tokens (should score MEDIUM-HIGH)\r\n    @{Token=\"Phase 1\"; Freq=136; CFI=0.96; Expected=\"HIGH\"}\r\n    @{Token=\"Architecture\"; Freq=80; CFI=0.75; Expected=\"MEDIUM\"}\r\n    \r\n    # Low frequency tokens (should score LOW)\r\n    @{Token=\"TemporalAttention\"; Freq=15; CFI=0.40; Expected=\"LOW\"}\r\n)\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Hybrid Scoring Validation ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n$highCount = 0\r\n$mediumCount = 0\r\n$lowCount = 0\r\n\r\nforeach ($case in $testCases) {\r\n    $freqScore = [Math]::Min(1, $case.Freq / 120)\r\n    $score = $case.CFI * $freqScore\r\n    \r\n    # Classify: HIGH >= 0.4, MEDIUM >= 0.2, LOW < 0.2\r\n    $classification = if ($score -ge 0.4) { \"HIGH\" } elseif ($score -ge 0.2) { \"MEDIUM\" } else { \"LOW\" }\r\n    \r\n    $match = if ($classification -eq $case.Expected) { \"✓\" } else { \"✗\" }\r\n    \r\n    Write-Host \"$($match) `\"$($case.Token)`\": CFI=$($case.CFI) freq=$($case.Freq) score=$($score.ToString('F3')) [$classification]\"\r\n    \r\n    switch ($classification) {\r\n        \"HIGH\" { $highCount++ }\r\n        \"MEDIUM\" { $mediumCount++ }\r\n        \"LOW\" { $lowCount++ }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Summary: HIGH=$highCount MEDIUM=$mediumCount LOW=$lowCount\"\r\nfile: experiments/hybrid_scoring_test.ps1\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:41:01\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774377665490}}
